attribute.name: Content Type
attribute.description: Controls the formatting of requirements, possible values are: PLAIN (the default) and HTML.

attribute.name: Enable Evaluation
attribute.description: Enables/disables the evaluation of requirements from the document.

attribute.name: Enable Suspicious Calculation
attribute.description: Enables/disables the consideration of the requirements from the document for the caculation of the suspicious state of elements that refer to those requirements.

attribute.name: Show Text Section IDs
attribute.description: Show the IDs of text sections within the GUI and the test reports.

requirement.text: The local function cil_ManageInputSignals will manipulate the PresfAct_Adj_ST3 input frame
The local function cil_ManageInputSignals will manipulate the Ign_Stat_ST3 input frame
The local function cil_ManageInputSignals will compute the Impact3_ST3 input frame
The local variable CIL_stPresfActAdjFrame will hold the value of the PresfAct_Adj_ST3 frame and be send though the application (presafe request signal).
The local variable CIL_stIgnStatFrame will hold the value of the Ign_Stat_ST3 frame
The local function cil_ManageInputSignals will manipulate the Bckl_Sw_Fx_Stat_ST3 input frame.

The function CIL_ComNotification_BltSlckDec_Md_Rq_HU_ST3_64a95ccf_Rx will manipulate the reading of R_BltSlckDec_Md_Rq_HU_ST3 signal. Based on this the BltSlckDec_Md_XX_Stat_ST3 signal will be computed.

CIL will save in local variable cil_u8BcklSwStatSignal signal Bckl_Sw_D_Stat or Bckl_Sw_FP_Stat from frame Bckl_Sw_Fx_Stat_ST3 depeding of the ECU location parameter NVP_u8ECULocation: and Configured Steergin wheel position from NVP_stVehicleEquipmentData.
The local variable cil_stImpactSignalsStatus2 will hold the value of the Impact2_ST3 frame
The local variable cil_stImpactSignalsStatus3 will hold the value of the Impact3_ST3 frame
The local function cil_ManageInputSignals will compute the signals from SBeltTens_SP_Lvl_ST3 frame.
CIL will handle the computation of signal Presf_Act_TensSupp from frame Presf_Act_Adj_ST3.
CIL will handle the computation of signal Isw_Ign_Stat from frame Ign_Stat_ST3.
CIL will handle the computation of signal Bckl_Sw_D_Stat from frame Bckl_Sw_Fx_Stat_ST3
CIL will handle the computation of signal Bckl_Sw_FP_Stat from frame Bckl_Sw_Fx_Stat_ST3
CIL will handle the computation of signal Impact RO Type1 from frame Impact3_ST3.
CIL will handle the computation of signal Impact RO Type2 from frame Impact3_ST3.
CIL will handle the computation of signal Impact_X_ST3 from frame Impact3_ST3.
CIL will handle the computation of signal Impact_Y_ST3 from frame Impact3_ST3.
CIL will handle computation of signals PS_CURVE(CIL_u8PSCurve) from frame BeltAdj_UI_Set_Rq_ST3
CIL will handle the computation of signal Presf_Lvl from frame Presf_Act_Adj_ST3.
CIL will handle the computation of signal Presf_Enbl from frame Presf_Act_Adj_ST3.
The local variable CIL_u8PSCurve will hold the value of the PS_Curve_FL_Stat signal if the ECU location is left
The local variable CIL_u8PSCurve will hold the value of the PS_Curve_FR_Stat signal if the ECU location is right
The local variable cil_u8ActivationRequest will hold the copy of the Presf_Lvl_ST3 signal value.
CIL will handle the computation of signal PresfAct_TensSupp_Rq_ST3 from frame Presf_Act_Adj_ST3.

The local function cil_ManageInhibitConditions will gather information read by ManageInputSignal and will compute or clear inhibition status for all cycles. Init value should be 0 ( no inhibition conditions)
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the tensioning cycles and release if signal Presf_Enbl_ST3 value is not 1 (is 0 or 3).

CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the release cycle if signal PresfAccelReset_NotExcd_ST3 is not 2 or 3 for at least NVP_u8PRESAFEAccelerationTimeout * 10 ms than smooth release shall be executed (after each PRESAFE cycle request on PRESAFE source (LEVEL 2 – HWA 1 is an exception) configured with next cycle) (is 0,1)

CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the release cycle if signal PresfAccelReset_NotExcd_ST3 is not 2 or 3 for at least NVP_u8Haptic1AccelerationTimeout * 10 ms than smooth release shall be executed (after each LEVEL 2 – hwa 1 cycle request on PRESAFE source configured with next cycle) (is 0,1)

CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the release cycle if signal PresfAccelReset_NotExcd_ST3 is not 2 or for at least NVP_u8APIAccelerationTimeout * 10 ms than smooth release shall be executed (after each cycle request on API source configured with next cycle) (is 0,1)

CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the release cycle if signal PresfAccelReset_NotExcd_ST3 is not 2 or for at least NVP_u8BSR1AccelerationTimeout * 10 ms than smooth release shall be executed (after each BSR 1 ALGO cycle request configured with next cycle)

If Release is still inhibitted by PresfAccelReset_NotExcd_ST3 after BSR1 was executed then after 60s an emergency release will be executed and inhibition will be cleared. For this variable cil_u16EmergencyReleaseCounter and cil_u8EmergencyRelease will be used to count the 60 s and to check if it was executed or not.
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the release cycle Timeout on PRESAFE FRAME CIL_bTimeoutError_Presf is received.
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the tensioning cycles if signal ISw_Stat_ST3 is not 4 (is 0,1,2,5 or 7 ).
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the tensioning cycles if signal Bckl_Sw_D_Stat_ST3 is not 0 (is 1,2,3) and ECU location is left.
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the tensioning cycles if signal Bckl_Sw_FP_Stat_ST3 is not 0 (is 1,2,3) and ECU location is right.
CIL module will request BSR1 execution (cycle 18) if value for Bckl_D_FP_Stat_ST3 is trasitioning from 1 to 0 and ECU location is left.
CIL module will request BSR1 execution (cycle 18) if value for Bckl_Sw_FP_Stat_ST3 is trasitioning from 1 to 0 and ECU location is right.

CIL module will request BSR1 execution (cycle 18) if value for variable NVP_u8BeltSlkDecModeis transitioning from OFF to ON with a delay of NVP_u8AfterMd * 5 time.Variable cil_u16ModeTransitionDelayCounter will be used and inhibiton of KU8_CIL_DelayModeTransition will be set,
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the BSR1 by ALGO if NVP_u8BeltSlkDecModeis OFF
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the tensioning cycles if signal Impact_RO_type1_ST3 is not 0 (is 1).
ORC profile , level 8 will be an inhibiton condition for all the profiles
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the tensioning cycles if signal Impact_X_ST3 is 1.
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the tensioning cycles if signal Impact_Y_ST3 is 1
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit the tensioning cycles if signal PresfAct_TensSupp_Rq_ST3 value is not “suppressed” on the specific side.
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit all cycles if following context are set. MMG_KU32_MASK_AEC_ECU_DEFECT_ALL_CYCLES | MMG_KU32_MASK_AEC_INHIB_ALL_CYCLES
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit tensioning cycles if following context are set. MMG_KU32_MASK_AEC_INHIB_TENSIONING_CYCLES
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit tensioning cycles if following group is set. KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_STEERING_CONFIG
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit BSR cycles if following context are set. KU32_CIL_MASK_BSR_INHIBITING_MODES

CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit PRE-safe cycles if the following groups are set : KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_IMPLAUSIBLE_DATA_IGNITION| KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_IMPLAUSIBLE_DATA_PRESAFE | KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_TIMEOUT_IGNITION
KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_EOL_MAX will be checked to inhibit cycles 4,5,6
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit ORC cycles if the following groups are set :KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_ IMPLAUSIBLE_DATA_IGNITION| KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_TIMEOUT_IGNITION
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit BSR cycles if signal PT4_PTCoor_PT_Rdy_ST3 from cil_stPTCoor4Pr5St3 is “0” or “3”
CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit BSR cycles if signals PT4_PTCoor_DrvPosn_Stat_ST3 from cil_stPTCoorDrvPos is “3”(engaged) .

CIL_u16InhibitionStatus will be set to inhibit BSR cycles if signal BeltHdOvr_FL/FR_Stat_ST3 from cil_u8BeltHandover is different than “0” and Belthandover is available .in the coding NVP_stVehicleEquipmentData

The local function cil_ManageAbortingConditions will gather information read by ManageInputSignal and will compute or clear abortion status for all cycles. Init value shall be 0 ( no abortion conditions)
CIL_u16AbortionStatus will be set to abort all cycles if following context are set : MMG_KU32_MASK_AEC_ECU_DEFECT_ALL_CYCLES
CIL_u16AbortionStatus will be set to abort tensioning cycles if following context are set : MMG_KU32_MASK_AEC_INHIB_TENSIONING_CYCLES
CIL_u16AbortionStatus will be set to abort tensioning cycles from presafe level if SNA is requested on PRE-SAFE level
CIL_u16AbortionStatus will be set to inhibit BSR cycles if signals PT4_PTCoor_DrvPosn_Stat_ST3 from cil_stPTCoorDrvPos is “3”(engaged) .

CIL_u16AbortionStatus will be set to inhibit BSR cycles if signal BeltHdOvr_FL/FR_Stat_ST3 from cil_u8BeltHandover is different than “0” and Belthandover is available .in the coding NVP_stVehicleEquipmentData
CIL_u16AbortionStatus will be set to inhibit ORC cycles if the following groups are set :KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_ IMPLAUSIBLE_DATA_IGNITION| KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_TIMEOUT_IGNITION
CIL_u16AbortionStatus will be set to inhibit API cycles if the variable CIL_bTimeoutError_API is true

CIL_u16AbortionStatus will be set to inhibit PRE-safe cycles if the following groups are set : KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_IMPLAUSIBLE_DATA_IGNITION| KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_IMPLAUSIBLE_DATA_PRESAFE | KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_TIMEOUT_IGNITION| KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_TIMEOUT_PRESAFE
Request sources have the following prio: ORC,PRE-safe, BSR, API, release.
CIL component will write the Buckle Door Switch value in order to activate or deactivate de BSR profile (cycle 26).
CIL_stManagedCycle will be used to store the curent executed cycle, the source of the request and the inhibiton status.

The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will manage release request (end of profile) when No cycle is requested according to the release inhibition status.If release is inhibitted/aborted it will be postponed/resumed when the conditions will disappear.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 0 when the tensioning level 1 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 18.19(HWA) when the tensioning level 2 is requested .
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 1 when the tensioning level 3 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 2 when the tensioning level 4 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 3 when the tensioning level 5 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 4 when the tensioning level 6 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 3 when the tensioning level 6 is requested and KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_EOL_MAX is set.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 5 when the tensioning level 7 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 3 when the tensioning level 7 is requested and KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_EOL_MAX is set.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 6 when the tensioning level 8 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 3 when the tensioning level 8 is requested and KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_EOL_MAX is set.
Cycle 4 instead of LEVEL 8 will be executed for NVP_u16TimeoutPresafe5 time. Counting will be done with variable cil_u16Presafe5Timeout.
After tensioning level 8, cycle 6, No Cycle will be executed until a new ignition run cycle. CIL_ CIL_u16InhibitionStatus and CIL_u16AbortionStatus will be updated accordingly.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 7 when the tensioning level 9 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 8 when the tensioning level 10 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 9 when the tensioning level 11 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 10 when the tensioning level 12 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 11 when the tensioning level 13 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 12 when the tensioning level 14 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 13 when the tensioning level 15 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the HWA2 cycle 20-21(HWA2) when the tensioning level 16 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the HWA3 cycle 22-23(HWA3) when the tensioning level 17 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the HWA4 cycle 24-25(HWA4) when the tensioning level 18 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the BSR1 cycle 26 when the tensioning level 19 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the BSR2 cycle 27 when the tensioning level 20 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the BSR3 cycle 28 when the tensioning level 21 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 14 when the tensioning level 22 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 15 when the tensioning level 23 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 16 when the tensioning level 24 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will activate the tensioning cycle 17 when the tensioning level 25 is requested.
The local function cil_TriggerProfiles will not activate any cycle when the tensioning level is any other value than the ones mentioned or timeout is received.

Variable cil_u8ExecHAPTIC_TYPe shall save which type of haptic will be executed (fixed / non fixed vibration duration) when this type of profile is requested. NVP_u8HapticType (NVP_u8HapticType (8 bits): HWA1 = bit 0 HWA2 = bit 1; HWA3 = bit3;HWA4 = bit4) to be used to determine the HWA type.
If HWA profile is configured with fixed duration HWA profiles shall execute their Vibration phase configured.

If HWA profile is configured with NON fixed duration, HWA profiles shall end when the requested HWA is removed from the bus or when the Vibration Phase configured is completely executed. For this , when no action is requested ( or other profile with lower prio ) HWA will end even if cil_u16HWACounter has not reached NVP_u16DurationHaptic.
The local function cil_ManageHapticRepetition will ensure the repetition of the vibration phase (cycle 19) of HWA1 for NVP_u16DurationHaptic1 (0x3E8) 1000ms time.
The local function cil_ManageHapticRepetition will ensure the repetition of the vibration phase (cycle 21) of HWA1 for NVP_u16DurationHaptic2 (0x3E8) 1000ms time.
The local function cil_ManageHapticRepetition will ensure the repetition of the vibration phase (cycle 23) of HWA1 for NVP_u16DurationHaptic3 (0x3E8) 1000ms time.
The local function cil_ManageHapticRepetition will ensure the repetition of the vibration phase (cycle 25) of HWA1 for NVP_u16DurationHaptic4 (0x3E8) 1000ms time.
CIL component will read the validity of the all implemented cycles
CIL component will write the haptic request in order to activate or deactivate the haptic profile (cycle 19).
CIL component will write the PreCrash Severity Level.
CIL component will write the Car Acceleration Low.
CIL component will write the Car Crash Detected.

Based on this R_BltSlckDec_Md_Rq_HU_ST3 signal output signal BltSlckDec_Md_XX_Stat_ST3 will be computed with help of variable NVP_u8BeltSlkDecMode that will be written with updated value.
Variable NVP_u8BeltSlkDecMode be set to - Off when Request is OFF (0) - On When request is ON (1) - Last valid value when request is SNA
Variable cil_u8Actv_Client will be used to store varible that will write signal RBTMxy_SP_ActvClient_ST35
cil_u8Actv_Client shall be 0 if no cycles is executed
cil_u8Actv_Client shall be initialized with 0x0f.
Variable cil_16Fct_Precond will store the value to be send on signal RBTMxy_SP_FctPrecond_Stat_ST35 from CIL.
cil_16Fct_Precond will be initialized with 0 (no conditions present)
Variable cil_16Fct_Precond will have the Bit 0 =1 if variable cil_u8BcklSwStatSignal is OK;
Variable cil_16Fct_Precond will have the Bit 1 =1 Belt Handover Extended is TRUE
Variable cil_16Fct_Precond will have the Bit 2 =1 if ERH group KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_SELF_PROTECTION is qualified
Variable cil_16Fct_Precond will have the Bit 3 =1 if ERH group KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_HARDWARE|KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_MOTOR is qualified
Variable cil_16Fct_Precond will have the Bit 4 =1 if KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_OVER_VO_TENS | KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_UNDER_VO_TENS is qualified or KL30 u16Voltage is outside normal range

Variable cil_16Fct_Precond will have the Bit 5 =1 if ERH groups KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_TIMEOUT_BUCKLE| KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_IMPLAUSIBLE_DATA_BUCKLE_ORC| KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_IMPLAUSIBLE_DATA_API| KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_TIMEOUT_API| are qualified or cil_u8BcklSwStatSignal has wrong value SNA,FLT or RBTMxy_SP_Lvl_Rq_ST35 has wrong value SNA and the source of the request is API

Variable cil_16Fct_Precond will have the Bit 6 =1 if profile requested is not implemented or if KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_EOL_LOW_HIGH, KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_EOL_COMFORT, KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_EOL_MAX are qualified and the source of the request is API
Variable cil_16Fct_Precond will have the Bit 7 =1 if profile requested is inhibited or aborted and none of the other conditions are detected

Variable cil_16Fct_Precond will have the corresponding bit set for KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_OVER_VO_TENS, KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_UNDER_VO_TENS, KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_EOL_COMFORT, KU32_AEC_GROUP_MASK_EOL_MAX, only if a belt profile is requested or active on API

The local function cil_ManageOutputSignals will be set RBTM_Disp_ST3 signal to 0 = IDLE if it is not enabled in the Vehicle Equipment 0x311

If several blocks are activated, cil_Update_07Cx_InfosToSend() function shall check which one is the next to sent.
If the bit 0 is set to 1, and the next bit to test is also bit 0, then cil_Update_07Cx_Block01_InfosToSend() is called to fill response with block 1 format.
If the bit 1 is set to 1, and the next bit to test is also bit 0, then cil_Update_07Cx_Block02_InfosToSend() is called to fill response with block 2 format.
If the bit 2 is set to 1, and the next bit to test is also bit 0, then cil_Update_07Cx_Block03_InfosToSend() is called to fill response with block 3 format.
If the bit 3 is set to 1, and the next bit to test is also bit 0, then cil_Update_07Cx_Block04_InfosToSend() is called to fill response with block 4 format.

Variables cil_u8PRESAFERequest or cil_u8APIRequest should ensure that if a profile is requested on PRE_SAFE or API and the execution is inhibitted, it will be postponed until all starting conditions will be fulfilled as long as the request is still active.

Variables cil_u8PRESAFERequest or cil_u8APIRequest and clearing the cil_u8TensioningAbortedStatus after profile was aborted should ensure that if a profile is requested on PRE_SAFE or API and the execution is aborted, it will be restarted after the abortion conditions disappear as long as the request is still active.

CIL component should ensure that if a BSR is request by ALGO ( on Buckle Switch / BeltSlackMode Switch) and it is inhibitted by : • Measured KL30 battery voltage is outside Normal Operating Range or • value received on CAN for signal PT4_PTCoor_PT_Rdy_ST3(only for buckle switch) or • value received on CAN for corresponding belt for signal BeltHdOvr_FL_Stat_ST3 or BeltHdOvr_FR_Stat_ST if enabled in the coding • value received on CAN for for signal PT4_PTCoor_DrvPosn_Stat_ST
execution of BSR will be postponed until all starting conditions will be fulfilled. For this KU8_CIL_ResumingInhibitionOfBSR will be used and cil_u8BSRBuckleStarted and cil_u8BSRBeltSlackStarted will be set accordingly.
